member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CrawlerName
member.summary: Indicates the crawler name when applicable. Returns NotCrawler when the device is not a crawler.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssBackground
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS3 background properties (such as background-image, background-color, etc.) that allow styling of the border and the background of an object, and create a shadow effect.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssBorderImage
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports border images, allowing decoration of the border around an object.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssCanvas
member.summary: Indicates if the browser can draw CSS images into a Canvas.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssColor
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS3 Color, allowing author control of the foreground colour and opacity of an element.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssColumn
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS3 columns for setting column- width and column-count.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssFlexbox
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports flexbox, allowing the automatic reordering of elements on the page when accessed from devices with different screen sizes.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssFont
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS3 fonts, including non-standard fonts, e.g. @font-face.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssGrid
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports all CSS grid properties.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssImages
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS3 images, allowing for fall-back images, gradients and other effects.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssMediaQueries
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports MediaQueries for dynamic CSS that uses the @media rule.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssMinMax
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the CSS 'min-width' and 'max-width' element.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssOverflow
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports overflowing of clipped blocks.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssPosition
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS position, allowing for different box placement algorithms, e.g. static, relative, absolute, fixed and initial.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssText
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports all CSS3 text features including: text-overflow, word-wrap and word-break.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssTransforms
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports 2D transformations in CSS3 including rotating, scaling, etc. This property includes support for both transform and transform-origin properties.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssTransitions
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS3 transitions elements, used for animating changes to properties.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.CssUI
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports CSS UI stylings, including text-overflow, css3-boxsizing and pointer properties.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DataSet
member.summary: Indicates if the browser has the ability to embed custom data attributes on all HTML elements using the 'data-' prefix.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DataUrl
member.summary: Indicates if the browser allows encoded data to be contained in a URL.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DeviceCertifications
member.summary: Indicates what certifications apply to this device.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DeviceId
member.summary: Consists of four components separated by a hyphen symbol: Hardware-Platform-Browser-IsCrawler where each Component represents an ID of the corresponding Profile.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DeviceOrientation
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports DOM events for device orientation, e.g. 'deviceorientation', 'devicemotion' and 'compassneedscalibration'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DeviceRAM
member.summary: Indicates the maximum volatile RAM capacity of the device in megabytes (MB). Where a device has different RAM capacity options, the largest option available is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DeviceRAMVariants
member.summary: Indicates the volatile RAM capacity options for the device in megabytes (MB). If no variants are found, then the value returned will be the same as "DeviceRAM".

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DeviceType
member.summary: Indicates the type of the device based on values set in other properties, such as IsMobile, IsTablet, IsSmartphone, IsSmallScreen etc.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Difference
member.summary: Used when detection method is not Exact or None. This is an integer value and the larger the value the less confident the detector is in this result.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Drift
member.summary: Total difference in character positions where the substrings hashes were found away from where they were expected.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Durability
member.summary: Indicates the device's Ingress Protection Rating against dust and water (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IP_Code).

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.DynamicContrastRatio
member.summary: Indicates the dynamic contrast ratio of the device's screen. This property is applicable only for TVs.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.EnergyConsumptionPerYear
member.summary: Indicates the annual energy consumption of the device per year in kWh. This property is applicable only for TVs.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.ExpansionSlotMaxSize
member.summary: Indicates the maximum amount of memory in gigabytes (GB) the expansion slot of the device can support.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.ExpansionSlotType
member.summary: Indicates the expansion slot type the device can support.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Fetch
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the Fetch API.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.FileReader
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports file reading with events to show progress and errors.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.FileSaver
member.summary: Indicates if the browser allows Blobs to be saved to client machines with events to show progress and errors. The End-User may opt to decline these files.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.FileWriter
member.summary: Indicates if the browser allows files to be saved to client machines with events to show progress and errors. The End-User may opt to decline these files.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.FormData
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the 'FormData' object. This property also refers to XMLHttpRequest. If the browser supports 'xhr2', the 'FormData' element will be also supported.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.FrequencyBands
member.summary: Indicates the list of frequency bands supported by the device.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.FrontCameraMegaPixels
member.summary: Indicates the resolution of the device's front camera in megapixels. For a device that has a rotating camera the same value is returned for front and back megapixels' properties.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Fullscreen
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports requests from a video or canvas element to be displayed in full-screen mode.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.GeoLocation
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports a feature to acquire the geographical location. For information on which GeoLoc API the browser supports, refer to another property called JavaScriptPreferredGeoLocApi.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.GPU
member.summary: Indicates the official name of the graphical chip within the SoC.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.GPUDesigner
member.summary: Indicates the Semiconductor Company that designed the GPU.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareAudioCodecsDecode
member.summary: Refers to the list of audio codecs supported for decoding by a Chipset. An audio codec is a program used to playback digital audio files. The values of this property are the codec's common name.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareAudioCodecsEncode
member.summary: Refers to the list of audio codecs supported for encoding by a Chipset. An audio codec is a program used to capture digital audio files. The values of this property are the codec's common name.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareCarrier
member.summary: Indicates the carrier when the device is sold by the HardwareVendor on a single carrier or as indicated via device User-Agent.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareFamily
member.summary: Indicates the name of a group of devices that only differ by model or region but are marketed under the same name, e.g. Galaxy Tab S 10.5.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareImages
member.summary: A list of images associated with the device. The string contains the caption, followed by the full image URL separated with a tab character.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareModel
member.summary: Indicates the model name or number used primarily by the hardware vendor to identify the device, e.g.SM-T805S. When a model identifier is not available the HardwareName will be used.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareModelVariants
member.summary: Indicates all model numbers used by the hardware vendor to identify the device. This property compliments 'HardwareModel', e.g. Hardware Model Variants A1660 and A1778 correlate to the Hardware Model - iPhone 7.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareName
member.summary: Indicates the primary marketing name associated with the device, e.g. Xperia Z5.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareProfileSource
member.summary: Indicates the source of the profile's specifications. This property will return 'Manufacturer' value if the profile data was obtained from the manufacturer of the device or the device itself. This property will return 'Authoritative' value if the profile data was not obtained from the manufacturer or the device itself but other third party sources (this may include retailers, social media, carriers, etc). This property will return 'Legacy' value if the profile data was obtained prior to 51degrees differentiating between Manufacturer and Authoritative. This property will return 'N/A' value if the profile data was not obtained due to unidentifiable User-Agent. The example profiles are: Generic Android Unknown, Unknown Tablet, etc.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareRank
member.summary: A measure of the popularity of this device model. All models are ordered by the number of events associated with that model that occurred in the sampling period. The device with the most events is ranked 1, the second 2 and so on.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareVendor
member.summary: Indicates the name of the company that manufactures the device or primarily sells it, e.g. Samsung.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareVideoCodecsDecode
member.summary: Refers to the list of video codecs supported for decoding by a Chipset. An video codec is a program used to playback digital video files. The values of this property are the codec's common name.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HardwareVideoCodecsEncode
member.summary: Refers to the list of video codecs supported for encoding by a Chipset. An video codec is a program used to capture digital video files. The values of this property are the codec's common name.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Has3DCamera
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a camera capable of taking 3D images.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Has3DScreen
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a screen capable of displaying 3D images.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasCamera
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a camera.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasClickWheel
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a click wheel such as found on Apple iPod devices.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasKeypad
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a physical numeric keypad.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasNFC
member.summary: Indicates if the device has embedded NFC (Near Field Communication) wireless technology.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasQwertyPad
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a physical qwerty keyboard.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasRemovableBattery
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a removable battery. This property is not applicable for devices that do not have batteries. Unless otherwise stated this property will return a 'False' value for tablets.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasTouchScreen
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a touch screen. This property will return 'False' for a device that does not have an integrated screen.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasTrackPad
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a trackpad or trackball. Examples of devices that support this property are the Nexus One and Blackberry Curve.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HasVirtualQwerty
member.summary: Indicates if the device has a virtual qwerty keyboard capability.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.History
member.summary: Indicates if the browser stores the session history for a web page that contains the URLs visited by the browser's user.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Html5
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the new markup in HTML 5 that also refers to 'New Semantic Elements' such as <header>, <nav>, <section>, <aside>,<footer> etc.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Html5Audio
member.summary: Lists what audio formats, if any, the browser supports using the HTML5 <audio> tag.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Html5Video
member.summary: Lists what video formats, if any, the browser supports using the HTLM5 <video> tag.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HtmlMediaCapture
member.summary: Indicates if the browser is able to use media inputs, e.g. webcam and microphone, in a script and as an input for forms, e.g. '<input type="file" accept="image/*" id="capture">' would prompt image- capturing software to open.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HtmlVersion
member.summary: Refers to the latest version of HyperText Markup Language (HTML) supported by the browser.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Http2
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports HTTP version 2.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.HttpLiveStreaming
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports HTTP Live Streaming, also known as HLS.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Iframe
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the 'Iframe' element, used to embed another document within a current HTML document.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IndexedDB
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports an indexed local database.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.InternalStorageVariants
member.summary: Indicates the internal persistent storage (ROM capacity) options the device can be supplied with in gigabytes (GB), including the device's Operating System and bundled applications. This could also be referred to as "Electrically Erasable Programmable Read-Only Memory (EEPROM)" or "Non Volatile Random Access Memory (NVRAM)". If no variants are found, then the value returned will be the same as "MaxInternalStorage".

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.InVRMode
member.summary: Indicates if a web page is accessed through a VR headset.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsConsole
member.summary: Indicates if the device is primarily a game console, such as an Xbox or Playstation.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsCrawler
member.summary: Indicates if the source of the web traffic identifies itself as operating without human interaction for the purpose of monitoring the availability or performance of a web site, retrieving a response for inclusion in a search engine or is requesting structured data such as via an API. Such sources are often referred to as crawlers, bots, robots, spiders, probes, monitors or HTTP services among other terms. Where the source pretends to be a device operating with human interaction, such as a smartphone or tablet, this property will return, 'False'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsDataMinimising
member.summary: Indicates if the browser may be optimised for low bandwidth. A true value indicates the browser supports a feature that can improve performance on low bandwidth connections, either via the removal of elements, features, a proxy or other methods.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsEmailBrowser
member.summary: Indicates if the application is an email browser (Outlook, Gmail, YahooMail, etc.) that is primarily used to access and manage emails (usually from mobile devices).

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsEmulatingDesktop
member.summary: Indicates if the mobile device accessing a web page emulates a desktop computer. This property is not applicable for desktops, media hubs, TVs and consoles.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsEmulatingDevice
member.summary: Indicates a browser that does not correctly identify the physical hardware device and instead reports an emulated device.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsEReader
member.summary: Indicates if the device is primarily advertised as an e-reader. If the device type is EReader then the device is not classified as a tablet.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsHardwareGroup
member.summary: Indicates a profile which contains more than a single hardware device. When this is true all returned properties represent the default value or lowest given specification of all grouped devices. E.g. the profile representing unknown Windows 10 tablets will return true. Apple devices detected through JavascriptHardwareProfile that do not uniquely identify a device will also return true, and HardwareModelVariants will return a list of model numbers associated with that device group.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsMediaHub
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a media hub or set top box that requires an external display(s).

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsMobile
member.summary: Indicates if the device's primary data connection is wireless and the device is designed to operate mostly by battery power (e.g. mobile phone, smartphone or tablet). This property does not indicate if the device is a mobile phone or not. Laptops are not classified as mobile devices under this definition and so 'IsMobile' will be 'False'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsScreenFoldable
member.summary: Indicates whether the device screen is foldable or not. If the device does not have a screen or the screen is not foldable, 'False' is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsSmallScreen
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a mobile with a screen size less than 2.5 inches even where the device is marketed as a Smartphone.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsSmartPhone
member.summary: Indicates whether the device can make and receive phone calls, has a screen size greater than or equal to 2.5 inches, runs a modern operating system (Android, iOS, Windows Phone, BlackBerry etc.), is not designed to be a wearable technology and is marketed by the vendor as a Smartphone.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsSmartWatch
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a web enabled computerised wristwatch with other capabilities beyond timekeeping, such as push notifications. It runs on a Smart Operating System i.e. Android, WatchOS, Tizen, Ubuntu Touch and is designed to be wearable technology.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsTablet
member.summary: Indicates if the device is primarily marketed as a tablet or phablet and has a screen size equal to or greater than 7 inches.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsTv
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a TV running on a smart operating system e.g. Android.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.IsWebApp
member.summary: Indicates if a web page is accessed from an application whose main function is not browsing the World Wide Web or managing emails, e.g. the Facebook App. The application must be downloaded and installed onto the device from an app marketplace such as Apple's App Store or the Google Play Store, or via a third party as an .apk file or similar. This property will return a 'False' value for mobile browsers such as Chrome Mobile or email browsers (such as Hotmail).

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Iterations
member.summary: The number of iterations carried out in order to find a match. This is the number of nodes in the graph which have been visited.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Javascript
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports JavaScript.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptCanManipulateCSS
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript that can manipulate CSS on the browser's web page.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptCanManipulateDOM
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript that can manipulate the Document Object Model on the browser's web page.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptGetElementById
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports JavaScript that is able to access HTML elements from their ID using the getElementById method.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptHardwareProfile
member.summary: JavaScript that can override the profile found by the server using information on the client device. This property is applicable for Apple devices which do not provide information about the model in the User-Agent string.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptImageOptimiser
member.summary: Refers to the JavaScript snippet used to optimise images.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptPreferredGeoLocApi
member.summary: Indicates which GeoLoc API JavaScript the browser supports. If a browser supports a feature to acquire the user's geographical location, another property called 'GeoLocation' will be set to True.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptSupportsEventListener
member.summary: Indicates if the browser allows registration of event listeners on event targets by using the addEventListener() method.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptSupportsEvents
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript events 'onload', 'onclick' and 'onselect'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptSupportsInnerHtml
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript that is able to insert HTML into a DIV tag.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.JavascriptVersion
member.summary: Indicates which JavaScript version the browser uses. The number refers to JavaScript versioning, not ECMAscript or Jscript. If the browser doesn't support JavaScript then 'NotSupported' value is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Jpeg2000
member.summary: Indicates the browser supports JPEG 2000 image format.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.jQueryMobileSupport
member.summary: Refers to the grade of the level the device has with the jQuery Mobile Framework, as posted by jQuery.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Json
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the 'JSON' object. This property may need a vendor prefix, e.g. webkit, moz, etc.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.LayoutEngine
member.summary: Refers to the name of the embedded technology the browser uses to display formatted content on the screen.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Masking
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the CSS-mask element that allows users to alter the visibility of an item by either partially or fully hiding the item.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MatchedNodes
member.summary: Indicates the number of hash nodes matched within the evidence.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MaxInternalStorage
member.summary: Indicates the maximum amount of internal persistent storage (ROM capacity) with which the device is supplied in gigabytes (GB), including the space used by the device's Operating System and bundled applications. This could also be referred to as "Electrically Erasable Programmable Read-Only Memory (EEPROM)" or "Non Volatile Random Access Memory (NVRAM)". Where a device has different internal storage options, the largest option available is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MaxNumberOfSIMCards
member.summary: Indicates the maximum number of "Universal Integrated Circuit Cards (UICC - more commonly known as, SIM)" the device can support including both removable and embedded. If the device doesn't support any UICC then a value of '0' is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MaxStandbyTime
member.summary: Indicates the maximum standby time of the device in hours. This property is not applicable for a device without a battery.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MaxTalkTime
member.summary: Indicates the maximum talk time of the device in minutes. This property is not applicable for a device that does not have a battery or support phone calls.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MaxUsageTime
member.summary: Indicates the maximum general usage time of the device in minutes. This property is not applicable for a device without a battery.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Meter
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports a meter element that represents a scalar measurement within a known range or fractional value. This property does not indicate whether the browser supports the progress bar indication. For this purpose, the progress property should be used.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.Method
member.summary: The method used to determine the match result.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.MIDP
member.summary: Indicates which version of Mobile Information Device Profile the device supports, used with Java ME and CLDC.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.NativeBrand
member.summary: Refers to the 'Retail Branding' value returned for Android Google Play native applications, when the android.os.Build.BRAND javascript is used to display the class. This property is not applicable for hardware running on operating systems other than Android.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.NativeDevice
member.summary: Refers to the 'Device' value returned for Android Google Play native applications, when the android.os.Build.DEVICE javascript is used to display the class. This property is not applicable for hardware running on operating systems other than Android.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.NativeModel
member.summary: Refers to the 'Model' value returned for Android Google Play native applications, when the android.os.Build.MODEL javascript is used to display the class. For Apple devices this property refers to the device identifier which appears in the native application from the developer usage log, for example 'iPad5,4'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.NativeName
member.summary: NativeName Refers to the 'Marketing Name' value that a device is registered with on the Google Play service. This property is not applicable for hardware running on operating systems other than Android.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.NativePlatform
member.summary: Indicates the name of the mobile operating system (iOS, Android) for which an application program has been developed to be used by a device.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.NumberOfScreens
member.summary: Indicates the number of screens the device has. This property is not applicable for a device that does not have a screen.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.Shared.DeviceDataBase.OEM

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.HardwareProfileSource
member.summary: Indicates the source of the profile's specifications. This property will return 'Manufacturer' value if the profile data was obtained from the manufacturer of the device or the device itself. This property will return 'Authoritative' value if the profile data was not obtained from the manufacturer or the device itself but other third party sources (this may include retailers, social media, carriers, etc). This property will return 'Legacy' value if the profile data was obtained prior to 51degrees differentiating between Manufacturer and Authoritative. This property will return 'N/A' value if the profile data was not obtained due to unidentifiable User-Agent. The example profiles are: Generic Android Unknown, Unknown Tablet, etc.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsCrawler
member.summary: Indicates if the source of the web traffic identifies itself as operating without human interaction for the purpose of monitoring the availability or performance of a web site, retrieving a response for inclusion in a search engine or is requesting structured data such as via an API. Such sources are often referred to as crawlers, bots, robots, spiders, probes, monitors or HTTP services among other terms. Where the source pretends to be a device operating with human interaction, such as a smartphone or tablet, this property will return, 'False'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsDataMinimising

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsEmailBrowser

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsEmulatingDesktop

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsEmulatingDevice
member.summary: Indicates a browser that does not correctly identify the physical hardware device and instead reports an emulated device.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsEReader
member.summary: Indicates if the device is primarily advertised as an e-reader. If the device type is EReader then the device is not classified as a tablet.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsHardwareGroup
member.summary: Indicates a profile which contains more than a single hardware device. When this is true all returned properties represent the default value or lowest given specification of all grouped devices. E.g. the profile representing unknown Windows 10 tablets will return true. Apple devices detected through JavascriptHardwareProfile that do not uniquely identify a device will also return true, and HardwareModelVariants will return a list of model numbers associated with that device group.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsMediaHub
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a media hub or set top box that requires an external display(s).

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsMobile
member.summary: Indicates if the device's primary data connection is wireless and the device is designed to operate mostly by battery power (e.g. mobile phone, smartphone or tablet). This property does not indicate if the device is a mobile phone or not. Laptops are not classified as mobile devices under this definition and so 'IsMobile' will be 'False'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsScreenFoldable
member.summary: Indicates whether the device screen is foldable or not. If the device does not have a screen or the screen is not foldable, 'False' is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsSmallScreen
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a mobile with a screen size less than 2.5 inches even where the device is marketed as a Smartphone.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsSmartPhone
member.summary: Indicates whether the device can make and receive phone calls, has a screen size greater than or equal to 2.5 inches, runs a modern operating system (Android, iOS, Windows Phone, BlackBerry etc.), is not designed to be a wearable technology and is marketed by the vendor as a Smartphone.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsSmartWatch
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a web enabled computerised wristwatch with other capabilities beyond timekeeping, such as push notifications. It runs on a Smart Operating System i.e. Android, WatchOS, Tizen, Ubuntu Touch and is designed to be wearable technology.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsTablet
member.summary: Indicates if the device is primarily marketed as a tablet or phablet and has a screen size equal to or greater than 7 inches.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsTv
member.summary: Indicates if the device is a TV running on a smart operating system e.g. Android.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.IsWebApp
member.summary: Indicates if a web page is accessed from an application whose main function is not browsing the World Wide Web or managing emails, e.g. the Facebook App. The application must be downloaded and installed onto the device from an app marketplace such as Apple's App Store or the Google Play Store, or via a third party as an .apk file or similar. This property will return a 'False' value for mobile browsers such as Chrome Mobile or email browsers (such as Hotmail).

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Iterations
member.summary: The number of iterations carried out in order to find a match. This is the number of nodes in the graph which have been visited.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Javascript
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports JavaScript.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptCanManipulateCSS
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript that can manipulate CSS on the browser's web page.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptCanManipulateDOM
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript that can manipulate the Document Object Model on the browser's web page.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptGetElementById
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports JavaScript that is able to access HTML elements from their ID using the getElementById method.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptHardwareProfile
member.summary: JavaScript that can override the profile found by the server using information on the client device. This property is applicable for Apple devices which do not provide information about the model in the User-Agent string.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptImageOptimiser
member.summary: Refers to the JavaScript snippet used to optimise images.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptPreferredGeoLocApi
member.summary: Indicates which GeoLoc API JavaScript the browser supports. If a browser supports a feature to acquire the user's geographical location, another property called 'GeoLocation' will be set to True.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptSupportsEventListener
member.summary: Indicates if the browser allows registration of event listeners on event targets by using the addEventListener() method.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptSupportsEvents
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript events 'onload', 'onclick' and 'onselect'.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptSupportsInnerHtml
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the JavaScript that is able to insert HTML into a DIV tag.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.JavascriptVersion
member.summary: Indicates which JavaScript version the browser uses. The number refers to JavaScript versioning, not ECMAscript or Jscript. If the browser doesn't support JavaScript then 'NotSupported' value is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Jpeg2000
member.summary: Indicates the browser supports JPEG 2000 image format.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.jQueryMobileSupport
member.summary: Refers to the grade of the level the device has with the jQuery Mobile Framework, as posted by jQuery.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Json
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the 'JSON' object. This property may need a vendor prefix, e.g. webkit, moz, etc.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.LayoutEngine
member.summary: Refers to the name of the embedded technology the browser uses to display formatted content on the screen.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Masking
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the CSS-mask element that allows users to alter the visibility of an item by either partially or fully hiding the item.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MatchedNodes
member.summary: Indicates the number of hash nodes matched within the evidence.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MaxInternalStorage
member.summary: Indicates the maximum amount of internal persistent storage (ROM capacity) with which the device is supplied in gigabytes (GB), including the space used by the device's Operating System and bundled applications. This could also be referred to as "Electrically Erasable Programmable Read-Only Memory (EEPROM)" or "Non Volatile Random Access Memory (NVRAM)". member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MaxNumberOfSIMCards
member.summary: Indicates the maximum number of "Universal Integrated Circuit Cards (UICC - more commonly known as, SIM)" the device can support including both removable and embedded. If the device doesn't support any UICC then a value of '0' is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MaxStandbyTime
member.summary: Indicates the maximum standby time of the device in hours. This property is not applicable for a device without a battery.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MaxTalkTime
member.summary: Indicates the maximum talk time of the device in minutes. This property is not applicable for a device that does not have a battery or support phone calls.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MaxUsageTime
member.summary: Indicates the maximum general usage time of the device in minutes. This property is not applicable for a device without a battery.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Meter
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports a meter element that represents a scalar measurement within a known range or fractional value. This property does not indicate whether the browser supports the progress bar indication. For this purpose, the progress property should be used.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Method
member.summary: The method used to determine the match result.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.MIDP

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.NativeDevice

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.NativeModel

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.NativeName

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.NativePlatform

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.NumberOfScreens

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.OEM

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.OnPowerConsumption

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PixelRatio

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PixelRatioJavascript

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformDiscontinuedAge

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformDiscontinuedMonth

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformDiscontinuedYear

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformName

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformPreviewAge
member.summary: Indicates the age in months of the operating system since the PlatformPreviewYear and PlatformPreviewMonth.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformPreviewMonth

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformPreviewYear
member.summary: The year in which the platform version was originally released as a Beta/Developer version by the platform vendor. This is before it is officially released as a stable version, to ensure wider testing by the community can take place.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformRank
member.summary: A measure of the popularity of this software platform (i.e. OS and version). All platforms are ordered by the number of events associated with that platform that occurred in the sampling period. The platform with the most events is ranked 1, the second 2 and so on.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformReleaseAge

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformReleaseMonth
member.summary: The month in which the platform version was officially released to users by the platform vendor. This version is called the stable version as any bugs or difficulties highlighted in the Beta/Developer version will have been fixed for this release.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformReleaseYear
member.summary: The year in which the platform version was officially released to users by the platform vendor. This version is called the stable version as any bugs or difficulties highlighted in the Beta/Developer Version will have been fixed for this release.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformVendor
member.summary: Indicates the name of the company that developed the operating system.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PlatformVersion
member.summary: Indicates the version or subversion of the software platform.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PostMessage

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Preload

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.PriceBand

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Promise

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Prompts

member.summary: Indicates whether the "Universal Integrated Circuit Card (UICC - more commonly known as, SIM)" is removable or embedded. If removable, the form factor of the UICC is returned.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Supports24p
member.summary: Indicates if the device supports 24p; a video format that operates at 24 frames per second. This property is applicable only for TVs.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.SupportsPhoneCalls
member.summary: Indicates if the device can receive and make telephone calls using available bearers without any additional software such as VoIP. Devices that support voice calls do not necessarily support phone calls.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.SupportsTlsSsl
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports TLS or SSL, essential for secure protocols such as HTTPS.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.SupportsWebGL
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports WebGL technology to generate hardware-accelerated 3D graphics.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.SupportsWiDi
member.summary: Indicates if the device supports Wireless Display Technology. This property is only applicable for TVs.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Svg
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports SVG (scalable vector graphics), useful for 2D animations and applications where all objects within the SVG can be accessed via the DOM and can have assigned event listener elements.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.TAC
member.summary: Indicates the Type Allocation Code (TAC) for devices supporting GSM/3GPP networks which come from multiple sources. This property will return 'N/A' if we cannot determine the device TAC authenticy.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.TouchEvents
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the method of registering and interpreting finder (or stylus) activity on touch screens or trackpads.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Track
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports a method of tracking text being played with media, e.g. subtitles and captions.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.UserAgents
member.summary: The matched User-Agents.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Video
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the 'Video' element for playing videos on web pages without requiring a plug-in.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Viewport
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports Viewport, to give control over view for different screen sizes and resolutions of devices accessing a website.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.WebP
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports the WebP image format.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.WebWorkers
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports background workers in JavaScript.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.WeightWithBattery
member.summary: Indicates the weight of the device with battery in grams.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.WeightWithoutBattery
member.summary: Indicates the weight of the device without battery in grams.

member.name: P:FiftyOne.DeviceDetection.IDeviceData.Xhr2
member.summary: Indicates if the browser supports client-to-server communication with XmlHttpRequests. If the browser supports 'Xhr2' will also support 'DataForm' element. This property may need a vendor prefix, e.g. webkit, moz, etc.
